There was yet another shooting today, this time at a church in California. It's heartbreaking to think of the grief these families are enduring. 

These recent shootings are why I'm committed to making gun reform at the federal level a priority if elected. We must see change now.

As I have traveled the state campaigning I have most enjoyed all the amazing people I have met and the stories I have heard.

To those who have told me they voted, or will vote for me, thank you for your trust and confidence!

If you have not voted be sure to do so on Tuesday! https://t.co/PtDdSvy5MD

We must not become desensitized to these stories, but we must keep fighting. It is time to see common sense gun reform enacted, not just talked about. It is time to acknowledge the evils of racism and take real action towards uprooting hate and pursuing healing.
